13 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 14A O.S. 2021, Section 2-211, is
14 amended to read as follows:
15 Section 2-211. A. With respect to all consumer credit sales
16 transactions, a discount which a seller offers, allows or otherwise
17 makes available for the purpose of inducing payment by cash, check
18 or similar means rather than by use of an open-end credit card
19 account shall not constitute a credit service charge as determined
20 under Section 2-109 of this title if the discount is offered to all
21 prospective buyers clearly and conspicuously in accordance with
22 regulations of the Administrator of Consumer Affairs. No A seller
23 in any consumer credit sales transaction may pass on the processing
24 fee or impose a surcharge on a cardholder who elects an open-end
